Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_tasks.model.notebook

Class Notebook

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_tasks.model.notebook.Notebook
  • public class Notebook
extends java.lang.Object
    Creates and controls an instance of notebook. Each notebook has a name, a ISortedList of Task Lists, a current task list, and an active task list. The class has the functionality to save a notebook to a file, add task lists to the notebook, get task lists from the notebook, and set the current task list. The specific functionality for the active task list is delegated to the ActiveTaskList class.
    Author:
    Anika Bhadriraju

    • Constructor Detail

      • Notebook

        public Notebook​(java.lang.String notebookName)
        Constructs a Notebook with the given name. The taskLists field is constructed in this constructor and the activeTaskList field is constructed and set to the currentTaskList. isChanged is initialized to true.
        Parameters:
        notebookName - name of notebook
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the notebook name is empty, null, or matches the name of the active task list

        public void saveNotebook​(java.io.File file)
        Saves the current instance of the notebook to a file. Works closely with writeNotebookFile() method in NotebookWriter class. When the notebook is saved, the isChanged boolean of the current Notebook is updated to false.
        Parameters:
        file - file to save the Noteboook to

      • addTaskList

        public void addTaskList​(TaskList taskList)
        Adds the TaskList to the list of task lists and sets this new task list to the current task list. The isChanged boolean is initialized to true. Error checking of the added task list is done in the TaskList class.
        Parameters:
        taskList - task list to add to list of Task Lists
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the task lists name is the same as the active task list or of an existing task list

      • getTaskListsNames

        public java.lang.String[] getTaskListsNames()
        Returns an Array of type String of the task list names. The name of the active task list is listed first.
        Returns:
        Array of task list names

      • setCurrentTaskList

        public void setCurrentTaskList​(java.lang.String taskListName)
        Sets the current task list to the AbstractTaskList with the name provided in the parameter of the method. If the task list is not found, the current task list is set to the active task list.
        Parameters:
        taskListName - name of task list to set to the current task list

      • getCurrentTaskList

        public AbstractTaskList getCurrentTaskList()
        Gets the current task list within the Notebook.
        Returns:
        current task list of type AbstractTaskList

      • editTaskList

        public void editTaskList​(java.lang.String taskListName)
        Edits the current task list in the notebook. Editing is done by removing the task list and adding it back to the task lists field after editing. isChanged is set to true.
        Parameters:
        taskListName - task list to edit
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the current task list is an active task list and if the name of the task list is the same as the active task list name or another task list in the notebook.

      • removeTaskList

        public void removeTaskList()
        Removes the current task list and sets the currentTaskList field to the active task list.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the current task list is the active task list

      • addTask

        public void addTask​(Task task)
        Adds the given task to the task list. If the task is active, the method adds the task to the active task list.
        Parameters:
        task - task to add to the task list

      • editTask

        public void editTask​(int idx,
                     java.lang.String taskName,
                     java.lang.String taskDescription,
                     boolean recurring,
                     boolean active)
        Edits the task by updating the fields of tasks with the given parameters. If the task is active, the method updates the fields of the task in the active task list.
        Parameters:
        idx - index of priority of the task
        taskName - name of the task
        taskDescription - description/details of the task
        recurring - true if the task is recurring
        active - true if the task is active
